.SH NAME
HTMLTableCellElement.cellIndex \- HTMLTableCellElement: cellIndex
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]cellIndex\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableCellElement\f[R] interface represents the position of a
cell within its row (\f[CR]<tr>\f[R]).
The first cell has an index of \f[CR]0\f[R].
.SH VALUE
Returns the index of the cell, or \f[CR]\-1\f[R] if the cell is not part
of any row.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example adds a label to all the cell numbers of the first row of
the \f[CR]tbody\f[R].
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]table\f[R]>
